> [!info]
> EORTC 26981/NCIC CE.3 (2000-2002) [Stupp NEJM '05](http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa043330), ['09](https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lanonc/article/PIIS1470-2045(09)70025-7/fulltext)

> [!rando]
> 60/30 (± TMZ → TMZ x6c).  

> [!summary]
> Stupp regimen is __standard of care__, although only trends to OS benefit for non-methylated tumors.  
# study
- 573 pts.
	- WHO 0-2. 18-70y. 
	- 16% bx only, remainder split GTR/STR.
- systemics
	- TMZ 75 mg/m2 qd during RT→ (1 mo break) 150-200 mg/m2 d1-5 q28d x6c. PCP ppx.
- RT:
	- GTV + 2-3 cm.
# results
|Results (mo)|RT only|+TMZ|
|---|---|---|
|MS|12|15|
|Me'd|15.3|23.4|
|non|12|12|
|OS 2y|11|27|
|OS 3y|4|16|
|OS 5y|2|10|
|Me'd|5|14|

- G3-4 toxicity ~7% (mostly thrombo/lymphocytopenia).
- HR-QoL [Taphoorn Lanc Onc '05](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16321761):
	- Groups favored the RT only group for social functioning at first follow up.
	- There was no difference in HR QoL thereafter.

>[!summary]
> - EORTC 26981 randomized nearly 600 patients who were treated with radiation to 60/30 to the addition of Temodar.
> - The results favored adding Temodar with improved MS from 12m to 15m. 
> - On subgroup analysis, though this effect was only significant for methylated tumors.
